<paragraph blockId="1.[264,1320,1153,1259]" pageId="1" pageNumber="62">Diagnosis: Sclerotized body with a short, conical gnathosoma. Dorsal plates foveate throughout. Three­segmented pedipalps dorsally attached on gnathosoma. Tibia I bearing an apical spine. Tarsus I with a heavy medial claw. Genua I lacks bipectinate seta.</paragraph>
